      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;overview&#34;&gt;Overview&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Attacker IP:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;code&gt;10.10.10.2&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Target Machine IP:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;code&gt;10.10.10.26&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The objective was to enumerate the target, identify exposed services, gain initial access by brute-forcing SSH credentials obtained during enumeration, and escalate privileges by abusing a misconfigured &lt;code&gt;sudo&lt;/code&gt; rule allowing execution of &lt;code&gt;systemctl&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://nvru.github.io/images/hmv/economists/vm.png&#34; alt=&#34;Machine information&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
